data.content:
These are two distinct C# 15 breaking changes:

---

### 1. `left && right` — dynamic short-circuit with interface `operator true`

`&&` desugars into calls to `operator true` + `operator &`. When `right` is `dynamic`, earlier compilers deferred everything to the runtime binder. C# 15 now attempts **static resolution** of `operator true`/`false` on the left operand's compile-time type (`IFilter`).

The problem: the runtime dynamic binder **cannot invoke static operators declared on interfaces** — only on classes. So the compiler rejects it.

**Fixes** (pick one):
```csharp
// Option A: use the concrete class type instead of the interface
void Apply(CompositeFilter left, dynamic right)
{
    var combined = left && right;  // OK — static op on a class
}

// Option B: avoid short-circuit; use & directly
void Apply(IFilter left, dynamic right)
{
    var combined = left & right;  // no operator true/false needed
}

// Option C: eliminate dynamic entirely
void Apply(IFilter left, IFilter right)
{
    // ...
}
```

---

### 2. `ref readonly` lambda — CS0518 (missing predefined type)

`ref readonly` return types on lambdas are new in C# 15. The compiler emits a `RequiresLocationAttribute` (or similar metadata marker) to annotate the synthesised delegate's return. That attribute must exist in the target framework's BCL.

CS0518 means **the attribute type isn't in your referenced runtime libraries**. This typically happens when:

- You updated the SDK/compiler to support C# 15 but your `TargetFramework` or runtime packages are still on an older version.
- You're targeting `netstandard` or an older TFM that lacks the new attribute.

**Fix:** Ensure your project targets `net11.0` and references the matching runtime:

```xml
<PropertyGroup>
  <TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>
</PropertyGroup>
```

If you can't retarget, polyfill the missing type by declaring it yourself:

```csharp
namespace System.Runtime.CompilerServices
{
    [AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Parameter | AttributeTargets.ReturnValue)]
    internal sealed class RequiresLocationAttribute : Attribute { }
}
```
